cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the intersection of computer vision and natural language processing, specifically exploring how language can guide representation learning in visual classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, since the paper also involves language processing, it could also fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes models that learn to perform visual classification while jointly predicting natural language task descriptions, which involves machine learning techniques such as meta-learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE).
